
Overview of noun powder

The noun powder has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (15) powder, pulverization, pulverisation -- (a solid substance in the form of tiny loose particles; a solid that has been pulverized)
2. (6) gunpowder, powder -- (a mixture of potassium nitrate, charcoal, and sulfur in a 75:15:10 ratio which is used in gunnery, time fuses, and fireworks)
3. (1) powder -- (any of various cosmetic or medical preparations dispensed in the form of a pulverized powder)

Overview of verb powder

The verb powder has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. powderize, powderise, powder, pulverize, pulverise -- (make into a powder by breaking up or cause to become dust; "pulverize the grains")
2. powder -- (apply powder to; "She powdered her nose"; "The King wears a powdered wig")
